1135
01:37:12,560 --> 01:37:15,221
We are working harder than we have ever worked before.

1136
01:37:15,661 --> 01:37:18,883
We are faced with challenges we have never come across.

1137
01:37:19,643 --> 01:37:23,025
Nobody comes and asks the educators how things are really going.

1138
01:37:23,765 --> 01:37:28,687
Does our central administration know how far behind these students are academically after this pandemic?

1139
01:37:29,227 --> 01:37:39,352
Do they really know that we are working miracles trying to back teach information while being told to use curriculums that are based on students having a solid foundation of skills?

1140
01:37:39,952 --> 01:37:50,717
Curriculums that were created pre-pandemic, built on assumptions that students have a certain base set of skills that would have to acquire during a succession of regular school years.

1141
01:37:51,317 --> 01:37:53,258
Has anyone told us what we can do about this?

1142
01:37:53,758 --> 01:37:56,159
Have we ever really received guidance on this?

1143
01:37:56,859 --> 01:37:57,860
The answer is no.

1144
01:37:58,520 --> 01:38:02,442
