1148
01:38:24,263 --> 01:38:27,227
And while central administration has taken steps to address

1149
01:38:28,731 --> 01:38:32,292
the emotional needs of our kids through responsive classroom and nexus?

1150
01:38:33,093 --> 01:38:36,714
Do they really know how things are going after this pandemic?

1151
01:38:37,134 --> 01:38:40,756
Has anyone really asked the educators if it's working?

1152
01:38:41,356 --> 01:38:44,537
Do they understand the trauma that some of our students have been through?

1153
01:38:45,077 --> 01:38:54,341
Do they know that we have students that break down regularly over not getting to be first in line or getting to have a certain color marker because their emotional needs are so high?

1154
01:38:55,021 --> 01:39:00,387
And does the administration understand that these students do not do not know how to be in school learners anymore.

1155
01:39:01,047 --> 01:39:08,996
Do they truly know that these kids are handling socializing difficulty after being isolated for so long, and from having so much screen time.

1156
01:39:09,637 --> 01:39:17,164
Do they know all the work the educators are doing to help their students in crisis that goes far beyond morning meetings and weekly nexus class.

1157
01:39:17,785 --> 01:39:22,707
The answer is no, because central administration is not present in our buildings to see this.

1158
01:39:23,387 --> 01:39:34,872
And does the district reach out and ask the teachers the ramifications of implementing the map testing upon returning from school in a pandemic, when our students are socially and emotionally at risk.

1159
01:39:35,552 --> 01:39:42,779
Have they asked about the students that cry because they're taking tests designed to give them questions based on material they've never been taught?

1160
01:39:43,439 --> 01:39:48,004
When teachers asked about this, we were told, hey, tell our students not to worry about that.

1161
01:39:48,664 --> 01:39:54,249
Does central administration know this isn't an answer to give an elementary student with high social emotional needs?

1162
01:39:54,850 --> 01:39:57,671
Do they know how hard this was for the teachers and the students?

1163
01:39:58,171 --> 01:39:59,392
Do they know about the tears?

1164
01:39:59,752 --> 01:40:01,132
Do they know about the meltdowns?

1165
01:40:01,692 --> 01:40:08,195
Do they understand the difficulty and struggle of computer testing kindergarten and first grade students?

1166
01:40:15,640 --> 01:40:17,261
And the answer to this is no.

1167
01:40:17,661 --> 01:40:23,825
Yet they tell us they understand how hard we are working and how hard things are for us, and they value us and all that we do.

1168
01:40:24,606 --> 01:40:30,370
