01:49:15,148 --> 01:49:24,292
And again, in December of last year, and ultimately came before your honorable body to request an increase in salary as a way to draw in qualified candidates.

1271
01:49:24,792 --> 01:49:27,273
Thank you for approving this on its first reading.

1272
01:49:27,294 --> 01:49:34,837
It's my hope that the council will approve the third reading of the increase in the near future, so we can retain the great candidate we did hire.

1273
01:49:36,025 --> 01:49:40,447
I take responsibility for what might feel and what was a rushed process.

1274
01:49:41,167 --> 01:49:46,069
It is and always is my intention to get the full budget to you sooner as I did the last two years.

1275
01:49:46,869 --> 01:49:56,713
We did meet the legal deadline, but the last two budgets and when presented did set the tone on how it should be done and we will strive to do that next year and into the future.

1276
01:49:57,878 --> 01:50:09,126
Over the past few months, city departments and school departments developed need-based budgets with requests to add to services that department heads recommend, and I too had hoped we could ultimately include.

1277
01:50:10,006 --> 01:50:24,556
Based on the school committee requesting approximately 4.5 million above the fiscal year 22 budget and city departments asking for a combined 1.7 million over last year's budget, plus increases in fixed costs totaling nearly 3.2 million,

1278
01:50:26,681 --> 01:50:30,943
We began with the proposed increase of 9 million above the fiscal year 22 budget.

1279
01:50:32,003 --> 01:50:41,887
I know that it's not new information, because I, along with the chief of staff, Nina Nazarian, have been in frequent communication with you over the last month regarding the fiscal challenges Medford is facing.

1280
01:50:42,588 --> 01:50:46,529
I was before you in early June and laid out these issues and was available for questions.

1281
01:50:47,690 --> 01:50:52,972
As we did for the fiscal year 22 budget, we are committing federal ARPA funds for revenue replacement.

1282
01:50:53,853 --> 01:51:09,697
However, because the allowable percentage to be used for revenue replacement is based on a strict formula that is designed to diminish year over year and is subject to strict federal guidelines, 7.2 million of OPERA will be used to support revenue replacement in this proposed budget.

1283
01:51:10,297 --> 01:51:14,798
This represents an approximate 4.5 million decrease over fiscal year 22.

1284
01:51:15,878 --> 01:51:18,399
This amount or close to it was expected, however,

1285
01:51:19,263 --> 01:51:24,330
because we knew we would have to wean off the use of one-time funds over the four-year period.

1286
01:51:25,501 --> 01:51:31,704
Thankfully, this $1 million budget isn't the only funding source that is helping move our city forward.

1287
01:51:32,625 --> 01:51:54,237
Instead, many critical and significant programs such as park renovations, open space projects, accessibility projects, funding for food insecurity, school projects like the McGlynn Playground Design Study, fire station renovations, historic preservation projects, funding to beautify our squares, housing support monies, tree stump removal, tree planting, and increasing

1288
01:51:54,822 --> 01:52:05,127
Our storm resiliency rely on alternative revenue streams, such as grant funding, CPA funding, opera funding, CDBG funding, and on-call casino revenue sharing.

1289
01:52:05,927 --> 01:52:16,012
Some of these funding sources were vastly underutilized prior to my time as mayor, leaving millions of dollars on the sidelines instead of being actively injected into our community.

1290
01:52:16,824 --> 01:52:19,965
It's important to remember, however, that spending money is not as easy as you think.

1291
01:52:20,785 --> 01:52:22,145
People behind me can tell you so.

1292
01:52:22,565 --> 01:52:25,346
We need to be hypercognizant of what is allowed by law.

1293
01:52:26,566 --> 01:52:31,407
We need smart, thoughtful input and guidance from our hardworking internal staff and external partners.

1294
01:52:31,988 --> 01:52:33,428
And we need the public to be on board.

1295
01:52:34,048 --> 01:52:38,069
We're making such amazing progress and are actively applying for more grants every day.

1296
01:52:39,312 --> 01:52:48,475
The budget presented to you today is a comprehensive and fiscally solid proposal that is firmly setting our goals and priorities for fiscal year 23 and beyond on a sound financial footing.

1297
01:52:49,336 --> 01:53:01,700
To give you brief highlights on some of the areas we're prioritizing in this budget proposal, in our parks and playgrounds, we are continuing to leverage a variety of funding sources to make upgrades to or fully renovate most of our open spaces.

1298
01:53:02,441 --> 01:53:06,082
We've already made substantial upgrades to the basketball courts at Barry Park,

1299
01:53:06,687 --> 01:53:11,671
placed at park, as well as expanding accessibility and inclusivity at places like Tufts Pool.

1300
01:53:12,292 --> 01:53:22,860
And I'm happy to say that we are renovating the basketball and tennis courts at Hickey Park, completely redoing Gillis in Carr Park, making improvements at McDonald Park, Riverside Plaza, and so much more.

1301
01:53:24,822 --> 01:53:28,405
We are committed to investing in our stump removal and tree planting operations.

1302
01:53:28,905 --> 01:53:33,869
We are a recently designated Tree City USA and will continue to strive for that distinction in fiscal year 23.

1303
01:53:35,185 --> 01:53:44,369
We're allocating CDBG funding to stump removal and tree planting, primarily in low to moderate income areas in the city, with additional tree planting and stump removal citywide.

1304
01:53:45,070 --> 01:53:57,375
We recently completed 90,000 in CPA funding for trees in our nine parks, including Morrison, and have signed to go to bond with an approval of 250,000 for stump removal.

1305
01:53:57,775 --> 01:53:58,816
Thanks to your approval.

1306
01:53:59,488 --> 01:54:05,430
And I thank you for that approval of the loan order, as well as the loan order to repair a million dollars worth of sidewalks.

1307
01:54:06,450 --> 01:54:12,011
We're making substantial progress, expanding environmental justice and creating a more sustainable and green future for the city.

1308
01:54:12,031 --> 01:54:16,313
We're adding the blue bike network into Medford on both public and private property.

1309
01:54:16,833 --> 01:54:25,255
And we're expanding our bike network by adding more bike lanes, sharrows and other necessary infrastructure to support safe options for biking in and through Medford.

1310
01:54:26,033 --> 01:54:30,736
With analysis and guidance from the pavement and sidewalk assessment, we completed and released last fall.

1311
01:54:31,237 --> 01:54:45,908
And by working with own work Tela and our new engineer and Tim McGivern, our DPW, we're planning and beginning to address the $175 million backlog of roads and sidewalks, repaving projects and upgrades that have been repeatedly ignored for decades.

1312
01:54:46,028 --> 01:54:52,693
And by using the right mix of preventative maintenance and addressing critical repairs first, we can and will begin to tackle this critical issue.

1313
01:54:53,522 --> 01:55:04,925
We are tackling climate change head on by working across departments through a municipal preparedness grant to improve Medford's capacity to prepare for and respond to climate-related natural disasters.

1314
01:55:05,786 --> 01:55:17,089
Through the MVP grant, we're devising plans for community hubs, and we are here to listen and to understand our community's experiences, needs, and ideas as we create better services together.

1315
01:55:18,009 --> 01:55:23,171
We are committed to expanding affordable housing options and limiting the financial burden on families and individuals

1316
01:55:23,653 --> 01:55:24,793
who want to live in Medford.

1317
01:55:25,294 --> 01:55:28,915
We have finalized and submitted our housing production plan to your body for review.

1318
01:55:29,655 --> 01:55:51,544
Additionally, in conjunction with our economic development team, we are continuing to fight for more oversight when it comes to 40B developments, but we've been negotiating with all three developers to re-examine plans that better fit the community's needs, and the ZBA recently announced that it remanded the decision on the Mill Creek development project, and we'll hear proposed updates at a meeting in the near future.

1319
01:55:52,568 --> 01:56:03,957
I'm happy to report that despite the self-imposed guidelines, the school committee overwhelmingly supported a 2.5% increase to the school's budget from fiscal year 22.

1320
01:56:04,477 --> 01:56:11,102
This expansion in funds ensures that our teachers, students, and staff have access to resources and tools that best equip them for success.

1321
01:56:11,903 --> 01:56:21,050
And thanks to the dedicated work of the school committee members, as well as the superintendent, assistant superintendent, and assistant superintendent, we're able to continue to invest in our schools

1322
01:56:21,980 --> 01:56:23,841
students and prepare them for the future.

1323
01:56:25,081 --> 01:56:34,226
Since I took office, we've taken a pragmatic and thoughtful approach to the city's finances, which has enabled our free cash reserves to be built up to the highest amount I can recall.

1324
01:56:34,826 --> 01:56:35,866
This is welcome news.

1325
01:56:36,487 --> 01:56:46,171
The next two years, however, will still be challenging in terms of our financial outlook and we will need to access the safety net when compiling the fiscal year 24 and 25 budget.

1326
01:56:48,556 --> 01:56:53,843
Though by then we hope to see some impressive commercial and mixed use development ready to open for the public.

1327
01:56:54,584 --> 01:57:02,695
I'm happy to announce tonight one of those developments will be a second retail marijuana establishment as the second contract was signed yesterday.

1328
01:57:04,458 --> 01:57:18,539
Medford's development potential is huge and developers in large sectors such as life science, manufacturing, biotech, and retail marijuana establishments are taking notice thanks to our efforts of the Economic Development Director and the Office of Planning, Development and Sustainability.

1329
01:57:19,305 --> 01:57:38,837
While continuing to protect and enhance residential neighborhoods, Medford's primarily commercial areas such as Mystic Ave, Wellington Circle, and portions of Mystic Valley Parkway and Medford Square are poised for new growth and strategic development that will put Medford on the map, increase our commercial tax base, and bring in new jobs and revenue to the city.

1330
01:57:39,417 --> 01:57:46,742
We are weeks away from putting out an RFI to developers to utilize the air rights we own above the Wellington parking lot.

1331
01:57:47,838 --> 01:57:55,402
We also have big plans in the coming years for a new future of our fire headquarters, more street and sidewalk maintenance work, and a new Medford High School.

1332
01:57:55,962 --> 01:58:03,406
Sustaining a high rating from our bond agencies is critical to supporting the debt we will bring on as a result of undertaking some of these key projects.

1333
01:58:04,847 --> 01:58:14,732
Although we may be going the route of funding a new high school using a request to our taxpayers by different means other than bonding, this is an effective and financially viable tool

1334
01:58:16,366 --> 01:58:24,489
In certain cases, building a future landmark educational facility that would be a gold standard in the state is certainly cause enough to explore this option.

1335
01:58:24,869 --> 01:58:28,770
I've talked about this vision with our community, our parents, our students, our teachers.

1336
01:58:29,630 --> 01:58:34,312
We have to be cognizant not to jeopardize our children's future in Medford by overextending the public now.

1337
01:58:35,445 --> 01:58:50,081
Going to the public today or last month for an override to increase the budget is not something ever requested of me by more than a few people, nor was it something I would decide on over the last few weeks without much thought, discussion, and deliberation.

1338
01:58:50,762 --> 01:58:52,704
It's not a decision I would make in a vacuum.

1339
01:58:53,713 --> 01:59:07,305
As I've said, there are many positives to glean from this budget, and despite the relatively modest increases, we're still able to provide the necessary services to our community, as well as continue to build upon several significant projects and initiatives from last year.

1340
01:59:07,685 --> 01:59:08,326
Almost done, sorry.

1341
01:59:09,107 --> 01:59:14,832
I appreciate the thoroughness and work you all put into these hearings, and I hope that you support this budget so we can get to work for the people.

1342
01:59:14,852 --> 01:59:20,757
I have many other projects to work on over the summer, and I know you have been hard at work on many things, including

1343
01:59:21,137 --> 01:59:24,499
deliberation of over 10 new ordinances yourself.

1344
01:59:25,260 --> 01:59:29,162
Let's work together to create a plan for our future needs starting tomorrow.

1345
01:59:30,163 --> 01:59:49,395
Lastly, I want you to know that I've heard you, I've heard our residents, I'm thankful for your advocacy, and I can now announce that this week we worked hard to adjust and formally recommend an additional $60,000 to part-time salaries for the library from negotiated salaries.

1346
