1844
02:42:18,804 --> 02:42:29,831
I want to spend every ounce of my energy teaching, but I am forced to spend my life bartending to sustain the vocation that I am talented at, the vocation that I love, and the vocation that is most useful to this world.

1845
02:42:30,837 --> 02:42:32,858
My students know that I serve and bartend.

1846
02:42:33,639 --> 02:42:36,761
They know I'm cranky on Fridays because I work the night before.

1847
02:42:37,041 --> 02:42:41,644
They know my back hurts because I stand behind a bar and walk to take orders.

1848
02:42:42,144 --> 02:42:48,408
They know it takes me longer to grade their papers because I was making drinks and serving food the night before.

1849
02:42:49,169 --> 02:42:54,912
Some have even come by the restaurant with their families and encouraged their caregivers to tip me well so that I can save money.

1850
02:42:56,913 --> 02:42:57,714
It's humiliating.

1851
02:43:00,652 --> 02:43:12,075
Knowing that I am pitied by my students and that I have to look into the eyes of their caregivers and show them what their school system has forced me to do is yet another exhausting part of my job.

1852
02:43:13,416 --> 02:43:15,776
I shouldn't have to serve my students' families.

1853
02:43:15,876 --> 02:43:22,038
I shouldn't have to serve school committee members or the head of the Department of Education, which I have done.

1854
02:43:23,430 --> 02:43:28,352
Yet I am failed by the superintendent, the school committee, and this mayor every single day.

1855
02:43:28,372 --> 02:43:33,734
I set a plate or a drink in front of them instead of getting paid a reasonable living wage.

1856
02:43:34,335 --> 02:43:37,196
I deserve a wage that reflects the increase in the cost of living.

1857
02:43:37,816 --> 02:43:41,278
I don't deserve platitudes about how there isn't any money for me.

1858
02:43:41,678 --> 02:43:47,280
Believe me, I have been aware of how little money there is for me the entire time I have worked this job.

1859
02:43:49,381 --> 02:43:50,602
I don't want your pity tips.

1860
02:43:51,581 --> 02:43:56,446
I want a wage that reflects the hard work and dedication I put into the Medford Public Schools.

1861
02:43:57,828 --> 02:43:59,950
Treat me with respect and let me teach.

1862
02:44:01,332 --> 02:44:02,533
Let me love my job.

1863
02:44:03,674 --> 02:44:05,657
Let me love and support your students.

1864
02:44:06,558 --> 02:44:06,838
Thank you.

1865
02:44:20,262 --> 02:44:21,062
Thank you so much.

1866
02:44:21,283 --> 02:44:26,386
I apologize for not saying this before, and I especially apologize for saying it after such a powerful speech.

1867
02:44:26,806 --> 02:44:33,210
If we could try to keep comments to three minutes just to respect the time, but that was worth every second.

1868
02:44:33,310 --> 02:44:34,310
Thank you.

1869
02:44:34,430 --> 02:44:35,731
Name and address for the record, please.

1870
02:44:36,732 --> 02:44:38,693
My name is Kate Willard.

1871
02:44:38,893 --> 02:44:45,337
I live at 10th Lawrence Street, and I have been a special educator at the Andrews Middle School for the past eight years.

1872
02:44:46,768 --> 02:44:56,596
I stand here today worried about the future of Medford students, as we teachers, paraprofessionals, and support staff are asked to do ever more each year with less and less support.

1873
02:44:57,538 --> 02:45:05,407
At the end of the school year, two exceptional teachers who have been in the district for 16 and 11 years resigned from my school.

1874
02:45:06,208 --> 02:45:17,420
While their colleagues, including me, feel their tremendous loss for AMS, their resignations were met with little to no acknowledgement from their administrators.

1875
02:45:18,858 --> 02:45:25,662
Both are moving on to other districts where they hope their profession and students are better valued and supported.

1876
02:45:26,123 --> 02:45:34,688
But our own students will now miss out on their positive community leadership and expert teaching because they did not feel valued here.

1877
02:45:36,203 --> 02:45:42,787
Due to resignations, retirements, and non-renewals, we now have half of our math positions to fill for next year.

1878
02:45:43,247 --> 02:45:58,596
Yet instead of supporting veteran staff or mentoring new teachers, the emphasis for addressing learning loss in math and other areas was on pushing more standardized testing on students we already knew were behind due to the pandemic disruptions.

1879
02:45:59,443 --> 02:46:07,731
This testing initiative was no more a solution to this problem than training teachers how to administer it was professional development.

1880
02:46:08,812 --> 02:46:18,081
It instead took time away from student learning and from more useful professional training to support teachers in the most challenging school year of our careers.

1881
02:46:20,000 --> 02:46:34,707
At the Andrews, we are now also down a PE and tech lab teacher for the coming year, making it unclear how our students will receive all of their STEM content or how one teacher can be asked to manage PE classes of over 40 middle school students.

1882
02:46:35,688 --> 02:46:45,233
We are down a student adjustment counselor when it was absolutely vital to fill this position this year for our most vulnerable students.

1883
02:46:46,487 --> 02:46:51,170
We had limited access to our own library this year due to staffing shortages.

1884
02:46:51,910 --> 02:46:58,475
Once an environment of vibrant learning and collaboration, the library stood silent and empty more days than not.

1885
02:46:59,175 --> 02:47:06,440
The only intermittent buzz being requests for Chromebooks, a task no librarian wants as their primary job.

1886
02:47:08,695 --> 02:47:09,815
You have about a minute left.

1887
02:47:10,235 --> 02:47:19,678
Due to a lack of planning for maternity leave, one special educator had to cover two caseloads of students on IEPs and inclusion settings this spring.

1888
02:47:20,178 --> 02:47:25,019
A planning solution for staffing I've seen more than once in my tenure just at the Andrews.

1889
02:47:25,759 --> 02:47:38,442
This kind of planning along with putting the burden of daily absences on other teachers instead of raising compensation to attract substitutes is why are we sure to lose more teachers in the coming years?

1890
02:47:39,683 --> 02:47:46,449
I've seen my school flourish, so the contrast of it quite literally falling apart has been hard to witness.

1891
02:47:47,030 --> 02:47:52,675
As of the last day of school, we have had a broken railing on a side staircase since February.

1892
02:47:52,695 --> 02:48:02,465
Our HVAC system left teachers and students on the third floor in temperatures above 80 degrees this spring, and we have cameras that don't work at key entry points.

1893
02:48:03,680 --> 02:48:15,706
This year, we have more behavioral referrals than ever before, many of them escalating further as the year progressed rather than subsiding as student needs are usually met through the development of appropriate behavior.

1894
02:48:16,906 --> 02:48:24,390
In all of these cases, those making decisions at the top are not in communication with those of us working directly with students.

1895
02:48:25,030 --> 02:48:29,372
They may hear our pleas, but their inaction shows they have not listened.

1896
02:48:30,172 --> 02:48:33,714
Staff morale at the Andrews and across the district is low.

1897
02:48:33,994 --> 02:48:41,257
We are burnout and exhausted from the stresses of the past two years, compounding on the already growing needs for our community.

1898
02:48:41,997 --> 02:48:48,440
If you truly mean to put our students first, please help us provide the education and environment they deserve today.

1899
02:48:49,253 --> 02:48:51,555
Thank you for hearing my colleagues and me tonight.

1900
02:48:51,915 --> 02:48:56,619
I hope you have listened and help us take action for the coming year.

1901
02:48:56,659 --> 02:49:02,445
Thank you.

1902
02:49:10,934 --> 02:49:13,494
Go ahead, name and address for the record, please.

1903
02:49:13,855 --> 02:49:15,155
My name is Maria Skiffington.

1904
02:49:15,335 --> 02:49:23,296
I've been a kindergarten teacher at the Roberts Elementary School for the past 16 years, and on my birthday in August, I will officially be a retired teacher.

1905
02:49:24,276 --> 02:49:29,357
I'm retiring from teaching about six years earlier than I had planned, and I wanna share why.

1906
02:49:30,477 --> 02:49:37,679
Before I do, I just want everyone here to know that I have truly enjoyed my time at the Roberts Elementary School, teaching alongside the best.

1907
02:49:40,116 --> 02:49:43,837
it's been an honor and a pleasure to be a part of that community.

1908
02:49:44,877 --> 02:49:51,879
As I stated in my retirement letter to the superintendent, teaching in Medford as it is today places huge demands on my daily life.

1909
02:49:52,519 --> 02:50:04,702
The recent proposal amidst contract negotiations to reduce prep time is a blow that indicates that these demands will continue to grow, leaving us with even less time than we already have for our family and for other fulfilling interests.

1910
02:50:06,321 --> 02:50:15,567
While working beyond contracted hours has been a growing problem since before the pandemic, the past three years has had teachers giving more than we thought we ever could.

1911
02:50:16,287 --> 02:50:20,050
Teachers turned on a dime in 2020 to get packets and materials ready for our students.

1912
02:50:20,590 --> 02:50:26,534
We worked with the children and their families remotely, learning as we went, trying to keep children engaged and learning to finish out 2020.

1913
02:50:26,714 --> 02:50:32,258
And we did all this while dealing with our own struggles with family illness, quarantine, and upended employment.

1914
02:50:33,577 --> 02:50:42,302
Whether you're a remote or a hybrid teacher, the 2020-2021 school year was the most intense, most challenging, and most exhausting year of our lives.

1915
02:50:43,122 --> 02:50:49,666
To facilitate this new way of teaching and learning without missing a beat, we collaborated on our plans and prepped after school and on weekends.

1916
02:50:50,386 --> 02:51:00,252
From delivering packets and materials to children's homes, troubleshooting technology, issues with family members, recording video instructions for the at-home cohort, we were nonstop.

1917
02:51:01,202 --> 02:51:03,946
We bought what was necessary to help these little ones.

1918
02:51:04,847 --> 02:51:06,429
I teach kindergarten, so they're five and six.

1919
02:51:07,250 --> 02:51:16,142
Navigate a desk, which they're not even supposed to have until first grade, keep supplies that they'd usually share separate, and show that they're work away from six feet away.

1920
02:51:16,162 --> 02:51:18,144
I'm sorry, excuse me, that's making me nervous.

1921
02:51:19,345 --> 02:51:31,413
Anyway, while our five and six-year-old children were kept at their shielded desks in the classroom, unable to share or allowed to play, distanced and isolated by necessity, we hope for your recovery in 2021-22.

1922
02:51:32,133 --> 02:51:34,095
Recovery is not what happened at all this year.

1923
02:51:35,215 --> 02:51:40,599
Still faced with the protocols of the pandemic, we are now expected to make our classrooms back to normal.

1924
02:51:42,500 --> 02:51:45,662
We are expected to do more while being told to practice self-care.

1925
02:51:46,082 --> 02:51:47,303
When are we going to do that?

1926
02:51:49,099 --> 02:51:54,623
It's questionable whether what we were asked to implement is even developmentally appropriate for kindergarten.

1927
02:51:55,223 --> 02:52:04,930
We learned and delivered a new phonics program that has children sitting in front of a projected screen of letters and words, performing repetitive decoding exercises for 20 to 25 minutes a day.

1928
02:52:05,791 --> 02:52:08,733
We administered online tests to children who could barely walk a mouse.

1929
02:52:09,647 --> 02:52:21,879
We worked within block schedules that meant giving up flexibility that's needed to review a difficult topic, provide support to that small group that gets pulled out, spend more time on something that grabs students' passions and interests.

1930
02:52:22,479 --> 02:52:26,743
And the one that gets me most of all is facilitating authentic play-based learning.

1931
02:52:27,564 --> 02:52:30,147
Everyone who knows me knows I'm passionate about Focus on K.

1932
02:52:31,702 --> 02:52:34,665
Focus on K was adopted by the district six years ago.

1933
02:52:34,865 --> 02:52:38,027
It is a plain inquiry based approach to teaching our youngest learners.

1934
02:52:38,588 --> 02:52:45,714
It incorporates all the standards of literacy, math, science, and social emotional learning into an authentic application of those concepts.

1935
02:52:46,314 --> 02:52:51,138
This past year, because of block scheduling, focus was watered down to being meaningless.

1936
02:52:52,279 --> 02:52:59,125
It's funny because one of the best things that focus delivers that central administration is supposedly so concerned about is social emotional learning.

1937
02:52:59,860 --> 02:53:07,283
With this approach, we don't just talk at our children about sharing, about the zones, about caring, about being kind.

1938
02:53:08,184 --> 02:53:16,708
With focus on, hey, children are encouraged to put those concepts into practice naturally, authentically, mindfully infusing their learning with their daily classroom life.

1939
02:53:17,508 --> 02:53:23,971
Here, the lack of time to teach children using developmentally appropriate practice was another huge factor in my decision to leave.

1940
02:53:25,092 --> 02:53:32,514
When I consider all the teachers and staff have been doing to get our community through this difficult and unprecedented time, I'm very proud to have been a part of it.

1941
02:53:33,495 --> 02:53:40,417
I have a difficult time understanding how we have gone through all we have without central administration respectfully acknowledging our hard work.

1942
02:53:41,368 --> 02:53:44,311
Showing respect is not just a line on a weekly update.

1943
02:53:44,691 --> 02:53:47,814
It's not a measly raise that doesn't even approach the cost of living.

1944
02:53:48,334 --> 02:53:49,695
It's not reduced prep time.

1945
02:53:50,096 --> 02:53:57,042
And it's certainly not referencing teachers as the ones who stand in front of the classroom, as we were in a recent budget presentation.

1946
02:53:57,482 --> 02:53:58,883
We are so much more.

1947
02:54:00,090 --> 02:54:04,312
The lack of respect is the reason for my decision to retire early.

1948
02:54:04,913 --> 02:54:07,895
Respecting teachers means really listening to teachers.

1949
02:54:08,335 --> 02:54:11,257
It means standing up and doing what is right for them and their students.

1950
02:54:11,917 --> 02:54:14,058
It means paying them a decent living wage.

1951
02:54:14,759 --> 02:54:17,780
Teachers work hard for the city of Medford in the best of times.

1952
02:54:18,221 --> 02:54:20,902
It's time for the city of Medford to give the teachers what they deserve.

1953
02:54:21,382 --> 02:54:24,965
And please, don't ask them to provide evidence that they're worthy.

1954
02:54:25,505 --> 02:54:28,667
The evidence is right there in front of you each and every day.

1955
02:54:29,436 --> 02:54:29,776
Thank you.

1956
02:54:29,936 --> 02:54:30,577
Thank you.

1957
02:54:43,845 --> 02:54:44,885
And just whatever, please.

1958
02:54:45,486 --> 02:54:47,247
Barry Ingber, 9 Draper Street.

1959
02:54:47,847 --> 02:54:52,790
And thank you, President Morrell and members of the council for this opportunity to speak.

1960
02:54:54,308 --> 02:55:09,221
I'm really wowed by these teachers and I'm actually changing what I'm going to talk about because I feel like there isn't anything that I can say that isn't trivial compared to what we've been hearing from them.

1961
02:55:09,802 --> 02:55:20,932
What I was planning to say was, it was something along the lines of, we need to raise the revenues to support our schools, to support our library,

1962
02:55:21,812 --> 02:55:27,216
and to support housing and to support all of the other services that we need and that are underfunded in this city.

1963
02:55:28,216 --> 02:55:31,158
And if you need to tax me to do that, tax me.

1964
02:55:33,079 --> 02:55:38,503
But I'm gonna address two things that you're not likely to hear from the audience.

1965
02:55:40,324 --> 02:55:49,530
One is, for a long time I've been hearing counselors talk about the need for having their own independent council.

1966
02:55:50,630 --> 02:55:57,792
And I thought that it was political grandstanding and I was wrong.

1967
02:55:59,532 --> 02:56:02,493
You guys do need independent counsel.

1968
02:56:03,733 --> 02:56:10,175
And I've experienced that as a resident activist working on ordinances where KP law has come in.

1969
02:56:10,755 --> 02:56:16,957
And instead of being helpful about how to craft a good ordinance has been obstructionist.

1970
02:56:17,832 --> 02:56:22,315
and has just gotten in the way of doing the work.

1971
02:56:22,695 --> 02:56:25,677
KP Law is not providing the services that you need.

1972
02:56:26,117 --> 02:56:30,580
You need a budget line so that you can have your own council to help you do your work.

1973
02:56:38,525 --> 02:56:44,549
Actually, I don't want to thank Councilor Knight for pushing on this issue over and over again.

1974
02:56:45,229 --> 02:56:46,290
I convinced you, huh?

1975
02:56:48,351 --> 02:56:53,555
convinced me, and there's times when I've convinced you of things, so back at you.

1976
02:56:56,117 --> 02:57:09,607
The other that I want to address is I recognize, and I think everybody else here recognizes how little power the city council has on the budget issue.

1977
02:57:11,988 --> 02:57:17,873
And the reason for this lack of power is our charter.

1978
02:57:19,025 --> 02:57:27,848
I ask you all to revisit the charter issue and to pass a charter review unanimously.

1979
02:57:29,689 --> 02:57:30,369
It will help you.

1980
02:57:31,209 --> 02:57:31,610
Thank you.

1981
02:57:31,810 --> 02:57:32,210
Thank you.

1982
02:57:39,052 --> 02:57:40,113
Name and address for the record, please.

1983
02:57:40,153 --> 02:57:43,434
Rebecca Johnson, 108 Floral Ave in Malden.

1984
02:57:44,114 --> 02:57:46,155
I brought my own timer because I'm a special ed teacher.

1985
02:57:51,345 --> 02:57:53,026
Good evening, members of the City Council.

1986
02:57:53,787 --> 02:57:59,491
I watched your meeting last Tuesday, and I'm here to tell you what years of funder funding has looked like for my students and me.

1987
02:58:00,192 --> 02:58:01,853
But first, let me tell you about my job.

1988
02:58:02,934 --> 02:58:06,757
I'm a special education teacher in the language-based program at the McGlynn Middle School.

1989
02:58:07,478 --> 02:58:13,642
This job is the best kept secret in Bedford, working with some of the best people, best young people in the city.

1990
02:58:14,524 --> 02:58:23,487
My students have a variety of disabilities which result in significant learning challenges, behavioral challenges, and other needs that make learning in a typical classroom difficult.

1991
02:58:24,228 --> 02:58:31,150
They work extremely hard and progress can be slow to arrive, but when they experience success, it's the coolest thing in the world to witness.

1992
02:58:31,750 --> 02:58:37,813
It's what keeps me coming back even when the challenges of pandemic schooling had me questioning my choice of career.

1993
02:58:38,913 --> 02:58:45,977
My students are the most vulnerable students that administrators insisted be brought back first when school reopened in 2020.

1994
02:58:46,717 --> 02:58:54,461
Administrators like to bring that up frequently as a point of pride, but when it comes to adequately staffing classrooms like mine, we hear crickets.

1995
02:58:55,142 --> 02:59:02,746
I heard you say last week that teachers are consistently asked to do more with less, and while for you that may be a talking point, it's my working reality.

1996
02:59:03,626 --> 02:59:11,073
When I was hired in 2014, the language-based program had three teachers, one for sixth grade, one for seventh grade, and me in eighth grade.

1997
02:59:11,654 --> 02:59:15,697
My second year, and every year since, we've been reduced to two teachers.

1998
02:59:16,298 --> 02:59:22,404
This means having multi-grade classes where some of our students attend lunch, art, music, P.E.

1999
02:59:22,444 --> 02:59:23,304
with a different grade.

2000
02:59:24,025 --> 02:59:27,546
One year we had a sixth grader attend an eighth grade health class.

2001
02:59:28,026 --> 02:59:35,449
Certainly not developmentally appropriate, but those situations will continue to occur when you're asked to do more with less.

2002
02:59:36,410 --> 02:59:39,471
This year we were short a paraprofessional for the last part of the school year.

2003
02:59:40,111 --> 02:59:43,432
We had a student move in with specific needs that no one could have predicted.

2004
02:59:44,012 --> 02:59:48,074
However, when your schools are kept at lean staffing levels, there's no one to call for help.

2005
02:59:49,074 --> 02:59:51,035
This is what the last few years have been like.

2006
02:59:52,051 --> 02:59:58,372
In my classroom and in classrooms district wide, paraprofessionals were consistently pulled from one assignment to cover another.

2007
02:59:59,032 --> 03:00:04,734
Robbing students in one class to serve the needs of students in another class puts everyone at a disadvantage.

2008
03:00:05,414 --> 03:00:13,675
Our students have very specific needs outlined in their IEPs and teachers found themselves constantly training staff that rotated in and out of their rooms.

2009
03:00:14,376 --> 03:00:20,697
Having to work with different people every day doesn't foster the type of student educator relationships that we should want for our kids.

2010
03:00:21,927 --> 03:00:29,570
In a conversation last week with a colleague, they said to me, those in charge will continue to understaff our schools because they know we'll make it work.

2011
03:00:30,250 --> 03:00:35,312
Educators always make it work because we have to and because the students in front of us deserve that.

2012
03:00:35,872 --> 03:00:43,515
However, doing more with less cannot possibly be the best practice for anyone and should not be the operating motto of the Medford Public Schools.

2013
03:00:44,035 --> 03:00:49,417
Thank you for your time and allowing me to share what years of underfunding has looked like for me and more importantly, our students.

2014
03:01:00,781 --> 03:01:02,422
Thank you, name and address for the record, please.

2015
03:01:02,642 --> 03:01:03,682
Yes, Audra Cashin.

2016
03:01:03,842 --> 03:01:08,064
I work at McGlynn Middle School, 3002 Mystic Valley Parkway.

2017
03:01:09,425 --> 03:01:23,311
Before I start, I was interested to hear that department heads have gone down in City Hall because I've been teaching in Medford for 24 years, and you should check out the school budget because the number of department heads has done nothing but rise the entire time I've been here.

2018
03:01:30,980 --> 03:01:34,424
I attended last week's budget meeting and wanted to begin by saying thank you.

2019
03:01:34,745 --> 03:01:38,409
I wanted to thank you for asking to hear from the teachers of Medford.

2020
03:01:38,669 --> 03:01:47,019
I have attended many meetings over the 24 years and last week's meeting here with you all was one of the few times I left feeling supported.

2021
03:01:47,760 --> 03:01:52,161
You repeatedly recognized the importance of funding education in Medford, but you didn't end there.

2022
03:01:52,422 --> 03:01:53,442
You asked to hear from us.

2023
03:01:53,762 --> 03:01:55,843
You asked for teachers to attend tonight's meeting.

2024
03:01:56,283 --> 03:01:59,364
I'm not sure you can understand what an impact that had on me.

2025
03:01:59,764 --> 03:02:02,945
When I arrived home and my husband asked how the meeting went, I replied, great.

2026
03:02:03,745 --> 03:02:06,046
His head shot up in disbelief and said, really?

2027
03:02:06,066 --> 03:02:08,167
He thought I was being sarcastic.

2028
03:02:09,207 --> 03:02:10,908
I realized nothing was settled last week.

2029
03:02:10,988 --> 03:02:13,628
The council made it clear you can only make recommendations.

2030
03:02:14,169 --> 03:02:16,089
So why did I find the meeting so encouraging?

2031
03:02:16,389 --> 03:02:17,590
Because I felt respected.

2032
03:02:18,370 --> 03:02:19,870
I knew you wanted to hear from us.

2033
03:02:20,330 --> 03:02:31,574
Lately, this hasn't been the case when it comes to central administration or school committee, which much of the time, Mr. Murphy's back has been turned to the teachers talking when he wasn't outside the room.

2034
03:02:33,113 --> 03:02:37,036
I received the emails from central administration saying how much we are appreciated.

2035
