04:52:39,732 --> 04:52:41,512
We can't even really reject the thing.

3272
04:52:42,172 --> 04:52:47,313
All we can do is say we don't like it, and then 45 days later, it goes no effect anyway, with a few cuts that we made.

3273
04:52:48,513 --> 04:52:51,934
So that's the power we have, and that's the situation we're in.

3274
04:52:52,754 --> 04:52:54,254
And that's why I'm not gonna vote for this budget.

3275
04:52:54,475 --> 04:52:54,795
Thank you.

3276
04:52:56,375 --> 04:52:56,975
Councilor Collins.

3277
04:52:59,208 --> 04:53:00,129
Thank you, President Morrell.

3278
04:53:01,269 --> 04:53:07,833
I just wanted to take the opportunity to make a statement on explaining my vote on this budget.

3279
04:53:08,353 --> 04:53:12,195
And before I dive into it, I just wanted to make it really clear.

3280
04:53:13,976 --> 04:53:16,657
My no vote is not personal.

3281
04:53:17,478 --> 04:53:22,901
It is not a referendum on the skill or the integrity of anybody in this administration.

3282
04:53:24,362 --> 04:53:28,284
It's because I see an unambiguous need for a bolder budget.

3283
04:53:29,638 --> 04:53:35,986
and I have to save my support for a bolder budget because I feel that's why I was elected.

3284
04:53:37,167 --> 04:53:44,756
Since before I sought office, I've been feeling alarmed by our city's lack of capacity for vital basic services.

3285
04:53:45,416 --> 04:53:47,919
If I knocked on your door during my campaign last year,

3286
04:53:48,580 --> 04:54:06,388
You probably heard me talk about my aspirations, for example, for the city to start an Office of Housing Stability and Office of Immigrant Outreach, for the city to be a leader in net zero development, invest in local public health resources, grow our tree canopy, fund a fully modernized website and on and on and on.

3287
04:54:06,548 --> 04:54:15,052
And my conviction that it is necessary that we push for more and better and more equitably distributed services in our community is why I'm sitting in this chair today.

3288
04:54:15,613 --> 04:54:16,393
I'm well aware

3289
04:54:16,933 --> 04:54:27,366
that list I just mentioned comprises some pretty ambitious policy goals and I am very, very well aware of the constraints that our city, like all cities, operates under.

3290
04:54:27,926 --> 04:54:34,074
We always have to be realistic about what is achievable in any given term or any fiscal year, but this budget goes far

3291
04:54:35,216 --> 04:54:38,499
below just being realistic and achievable.

3292
04:54:39,199 --> 04:54:45,104
This budget does not, to me, address the bare bones, basic, uncontroversial fundamentals.

3293
04:54:45,965 --> 04:54:47,386
We're not looking up at the ceiling.

3294
04:54:47,746 --> 04:54:48,767
We are looking up at the floor.

3295
04:54:50,781 --> 04:55:11,059
I believe that all of us are painfully aware of just how much we have to build up just to get back to baseline, to recover from the past two and a half years, to repair our roads and sidewalks and municipal infrastructure, to support those who are at risk of getting priced out of this community, to build a more resilient future, to take care of all of our residents the way that they deserve.

3296
04:55:12,138 --> 04:55:25,823
And it is all urgently necessary work it's urgently necessary work that feels to me unacceptably out of reach, because this budget doesn't even address the basics that our community needs and deserves this year right now.

3297
04:55:27,947 --> 04:55:30,868
just to restate some of what's been already put on the record tonight.

3298
04:55:31,728 --> 04:55:39,411
While students, teachers, and education staff are yearning to recover from the trauma and the substantial learning loss of the pandemic, the schools are level funded.

3299
04:55:40,132 --> 04:55:44,733
And in an environment of 8.5% inflation, level funding means less.

3300
04:55:45,353 --> 04:55:49,315
Less support for staff, less staff in the buildings, less support for students.

3301
04:55:50,563 --> 04:55:59,887
We spent years building a beautiful, brilliant new public library, and everybody chipped in, all through their taxes, and many with extra generosity on top.

3302
04:56:00,767 --> 04:56:03,749
And under this budget, we can't fully staff it.

3303
04:56:04,949 --> 04:56:07,210
Again, level funding means less service.

3304
04:56:08,768 --> 04:56:25,471
Thanks to community advocates translation services did occupy a place in the city's operating budget, which brought us closer to the goal of enabling all Metro residents to start to participate in city meetings, be equitable, equitably served by city communications, a goal which is still not really fully realized.

3305
04:56:26,452 --> 04:56:31,416
but in this budget proposal, there wasn't even room for translation services anymore.

3306
04:56:31,476 --> 04:56:37,100
It's been shifted to one-time funding, ARPA, which, as has been stated, expires in December of 2024.

3307
04:56:38,481 --> 04:56:49,610
Something so fundamental as making sure that what comes out of City Call will be receivable and intelligible by all constituents has no place being relegated to one-time funding services.

3308
04:56:51,231 --> 04:56:53,593
Finally, this City Council

3309
04:56:54,137 --> 04:56:59,539
is where residents come to advocate for any number of issues facing the community, from potholes to public safety to public health.

3310
04:57:00,579 --> 04:57:14,603
The channel that we have to respond to those issues with is our power to legislate, to craft ordinances and zoning that reflect our city's wants and needs, to enforce our standards for a safe city and organize for a livable future.

3311
04:57:16,744 --> 04:57:20,925
But with no dedicated legal staff for the council, after many, many requests,

3312
04:57:22,052 --> 04:57:30,899
and our critical phase two of zoning going, you know, without a commitment, we aren't being given the necessary tools to do this job.

3313
04:57:31,660 --> 04:57:41,568
I want to know how to be an effective legislator when we have to join a week's long queue to get a legal opinion on an ordinance, which has been my lived experience in the first six months of my term.

3314
04:57:42,450 --> 04:57:59,026
I want to know how to craft smart and thoughtful zoning reforms that will protect us in the climate change future when we don't have $50,000 for a zoning consultant, which for context is .025% of our current operating budget proposed for next fiscal year.

3315
04:57:59,727 --> 04:58:00,207
These are not

3316
04:58:01,246 --> 04:58:07,049
To me, trivial or petty matters, matters of convenience for me and my fellow councilors.

3317
04:58:07,750 --> 04:58:08,470
It's more important.

3318
04:58:08,510 --> 04:58:18,455
Those hampers are the only channel that this body has to address issues like housing stability, tree canopy, environmental standards, language accessibility, infrastructure safety, and on and on.

3319
04:58:19,356 --> 04:58:22,998
When the city council is denied tools to be effective, the community loses its advocate.

3320
04:58:24,790 --> 04:58:32,617
I know that even under ideal circumstances, we cannot do or even start all that needs to be done in a single year.

3321
04:58:33,398 --> 04:58:42,646
But this administration had told us explicitly that this year, the city is expected to do more with less, and that the plan for next year is to make do with potentially even less than that.

3322
04:58:43,687 --> 04:58:46,989
I cannot condone that plan, and I cannot condone that trajectory.

3323
04:58:47,049 --> 04:58:49,532
The stakes are too high, and the needs are too great.

3324
04:58:50,656 --> 04:58:59,424
I know that because we've been hearing from you and not just about the library and the schools and how hard it is to give our municipal workers the pay and the support that they deserve.

3325
04:59:00,405 --> 04:59:08,773
I hear from you about afterschool and infrastructure and basic constituent services and housing stability resources that you need and we cannot provide.

3326
04:59:10,335 --> 04:59:11,196
I need a commitment.

3327
04:59:12,368 --> 04:59:22,291
that the unassailable values that this administration promotes, like equity, security, sustainability, inclusion, that these are values in practice and not just awards.

3328
04:59:23,231 --> 04:59:25,052
And this budget does not yet make that commitment.

3329
04:59:26,292 --> 04:59:32,974
I desperately wanna see a budget proposal that makes a good faith effort at exemplifying those values that goes further.

3330
04:59:33,955 --> 04:59:41,377
I wanna see a proposal that says, we will move heaven and earth to fund our schools and our community spaces and acknowledges that we cannot afford to defer

3331
04:59:42,448 --> 04:59:48,772
on climate change and represents a real plan for making this community better every year, supporting all Medford residents the way they deserve.

3332
04:59:49,913 --> 04:59:51,134
But I haven't seen that plan yet.

3333
04:59:52,415 --> 04:59:56,077
When I do, and I hope I see it soon, I will vote yes on it.

3334
04:59:56,918 --> 05:00:01,921
And then I will work with my fellow counselors and this administration to make those values manifest in our community.

3335
05:00:02,822 --> 05:00:09,767
Because throughout this term so far, I can confidently say that this council has sought a collaborative approach with this administration.

3336
05:00:12,088 --> 05:00:19,310
But this is a moment where we must insist on reciprocity and collaboration in the service of our critical goals for the community.

3337
05:00:20,850 --> 05:00:24,351
Because what I'm waiting for is what the community is calling out for.

3338
05:00:25,411 --> 05:00:28,852
In sum, this budget, less than we deserve, less than we need.

3339
05:00:28,872 --> 05:00:33,773
I wish that we had the opportunity to negotiate about this, to dive into these questions.

3340
05:00:35,105 --> 05:00:36,426
weeks ago, months ago.

3341
05:00:36,926 --> 05:00:38,347
This is not the process that I wanted.

3342
05:00:39,288 --> 05:00:40,649
This is not the tone that I wanted.

3343
05:00:40,909 --> 05:00:41,810
I don't like any of this.

3344
05:00:43,030 --> 05:00:48,074
But I know that we have options for doing better for next year, but also for fiscal year 23.

3345
05:00:48,714 --> 05:00:50,295
And that's why I can't accept this proposal.

3346
05:00:50,555 --> 05:00:51,976
And that's why I'll be voting no on the budget.

3347
05:00:52,417 --> 05:00:53,377
Thank you for letting me take the time.

3348
05:00:53,397 --> 05:00:56,219
Thank you, Councilor Collins.

3349
05:00:56,439 --> 05:00:59,822
Councilor Svang, I know Councilors have some kind of closing statements.

3350
05:00:59,842 --> 05:01:00,182
It's just

3351
05:01:02,340 --> 05:01:03,141
It's 12, 11 a.m.

3352
05:01:04,062 --> 05:01:08,247
Does Shane get paid for next day now?

3353
05:01:08,287 --> 05:01:09,769
Because he's been here for two days.

3354
05:01:09,969 --> 05:01:12,072
So Shane should definitely get paid twice.

3355
05:01:16,413 --> 05:01:16,813
Thank you.

3356
05:01:16,833 --> 05:01:23,915
I didn't speak too much today because I wanted to make sure the public had a chance to speak, and I didn't want to belabor too many points.

3357
05:01:24,595 --> 05:01:32,998
I wanted to come before you all here today and tell you about how our city really dreamed big and how we created a budget that really combined ambition and actionability.

3358
05:01:33,738 --> 05:01:37,899
But unfortunately, these last two weeks of budget hearings have been grim.

3359
05:01:38,999 --> 05:01:44,701
Lack of transparency and lack of revenue means that we've been put in a difficult last-minute budget crisis.

3360
05:01:45,827 --> 05:01:50,292
Um, and we are we on the council are just as frustrated as you residents are.

3361
05:01:51,253 --> 05:01:53,455
We keep hearing that this is a pandemic problem.

3362
05:01:53,475 --> 05:02:04,246
But the reality is that we're two and a half years to a pandemic that's affected every single city in this Commonwealth and Medford and yet Medford is unique in facing a crisis like this.

3363
05:02:05,154 --> 05:02:15,602
In the past few months that I've been on city council, I've worked particularly hard to foster a friendly and cooperative environment, especially with the mayor's office.

3364
05:02:15,782 --> 05:02:25,029
And I've worked hard to recognize shared priorities, the housing production plan, the comprehensive plan, climate action plan, improving diversity and equity.

3365
05:02:25,770 --> 05:02:29,633
And I've worked very hard to operate in good faith, taking

3366
05:02:30,353 --> 05:02:36,738
you know, even taking some pretty difficult votes, which mainly supported the mayor's priorities.

3367
05:02:38,019 --> 05:02:47,207
I've tried to be reasonable and open-minded with the red lines and requests, making sure that they're, you know, they are actionable, they are achievable.

3368
05:02:47,787 --> 05:02:54,093
And over the last few weeks, I've asked future-focused questions about our department's plans and ambitions to improve our city,

3369
05:02:54,733 --> 05:02:58,356
And the answer through our many, many hours of meetings is clear.

3370
05:02:58,756 --> 05:03:13,447
We have volunteers, we have employees, and we have department heads who are flush with ideas about how we can improve city services, and how we can lift up the standards of living, and how we can ensure that Medford is safe, just, and inclusive.

3371
05:03:14,167 --> 05:03:18,490
But the true Grim Reaper that we face is not a city unwilling to move forward.

3372
05:03:18,791 --> 05:03:22,954
The true Grim Reaper we face are budgets that box us in.

3373
05:03:23,994 --> 05:03:26,916
which is unfortunately what is on the agenda tonight.

3374
05:03:27,816 --> 05:03:31,959
I understand where the mayor's coming from, I understand that this was a difficult budget to put together.

3375
05:03:32,559 --> 05:03:37,882
And I thank the mayor for calling for calling me today and for talking through my concerns.

3376
05:03:40,360 --> 05:03:43,161
you know, we're elected to make difficult choices.

3377
05:03:43,821 --> 05:03:49,323
I've been, I haven't slept more than five hours a night since the beginning of the month.

3378
05:03:51,184 --> 05:03:57,846
But, you know, for the sake of transparency, I do want, I can't conscionably vote yes on this budget.

3379
05:03:59,527 --> 05:04:07,130
you know, there's just some of the simple priorities, right, that we on the council have been talking about, and those on the school committee have asked as basic asks.

3380
05:04:08,430 --> 05:04:20,935
And, you know, this budget doesn't even really delve into the more ambitious concerns about investments in true community safety, the expanding translation programs, veterans programming, etc.

3381
05:04:22,636 --> 05:04:32,190
Those of you who've tuned into city council meetings before know that at the end of the day, when they take a difficult vote, there's really one question, there's one litmus test for me.

3382
05:04:32,951 --> 05:04:36,896
And that question is, does this improve the lives of the residents of our city?

3383
05:04:39,186 --> 05:04:40,927
You know, the answer tonight is regrettably no.

3384
05:04:41,587 --> 05:04:49,130
I don't think this budget as it is would help the longtime resident for whom our roads and sidewalks now pose a challenge to accessibility.

3385
05:04:49,210 --> 05:04:55,513
It wouldn't help the veteran or the new college student coming home who can't afford to settle down here in their hometown.

3386
05:04:56,033 --> 05:04:59,074
And it wouldn't help the renter who's facing an eviction notice.

3387
05:04:59,754 --> 05:05:05,857
It wouldn't necessarily help the parent and child who are catching up on elementary math after two years of the pandemic.

3388
05:05:06,358 --> 05:05:16,963
and it wouldn't help the black, brown, or Asian people in our city who are facing threats of safety and violence.

3389
05:05:17,323 --> 05:05:21,765
We as a council, we're ready for the difficult conversations to get our city back on track.

3390
05:05:22,445 --> 05:05:29,748
And perhaps most importantly, we are ready, and at least personally speaking, I'm excited to work with the city administration to find a way forward.

3391
05:05:30,749 --> 05:05:31,629
But the clock is ticking.

3392
05:05:32,269 --> 05:05:34,810
We have little time to solve a financial conundrum.

3393
05:05:38,011 --> 05:05:44,005
We're, you know, I think everyone's expressed this we just don't we it sucks we don't want to be in this position, but.

3394
05:05:45,003 --> 05:05:53,751
The measures that we've had to take are the only tools that we have as a city council to try to get a budget that's even better for our city.

3395
05:05:54,451 --> 05:06:00,877
This is our only chance for us to build that more ambitious city that we want.

3396
05:06:01,417 --> 05:06:07,622
Again, many of this administration's stated goals and plans are plans that I support and wish to see come true.

3397
05:06:08,403 --> 05:06:13,006
but these plans will remain mere wishes if we don't have the tools to put them into action.

3398
05:06:13,366 --> 05:06:14,467
And that's what I'm asking for.

3399
05:06:14,967 --> 05:06:18,669
Simple, low cost tools that will let us advance our shared priorities.

3400
05:06:19,930 --> 05:06:29,436
I hope in the next few days that we can all work together to get ourselves out of the situation and to advance our shared priorities and goals.

3401
05:06:29,976 --> 05:06:30,296
Thank you.

3402
05:06:31,537 --> 05:06:33,778
Any further discussion from the council?

3403
05:06:34,319 --> 05:06:34,759
Councilor Knight.

3404
05:06:35,262 --> 05:06:36,564
Madam President, thank you very much.

3405
05:06:37,685 --> 05:06:45,816
First of all, I think this council owes you a debt of gratitude because it wouldn't be where we are today, if it wasn't for your persistence.

3406
05:06:46,657 --> 05:06:50,302
You're not allowed to sit down we're going to give you what you want the big seat you got to stand up.

3407
05:06:52,424 --> 05:06:55,506
But we wouldn't be here today if it wasn't for your persistence.

3408
05:06:55,967 --> 05:07:01,170
Since your election as council president, you've been across the hall banging on the door saying, when are we going to start the budget hearings?

3409
05:07:01,191 --> 05:07:02,331
When are we going to start the budget hearings?

3410
05:07:02,351 --> 05:07:03,432
When are we going to start the budget hearings?

3411
05:07:03,873 --> 05:07:08,596
And it's because of that persistence that we're able to make the decisions that we've made tonight.

3412
05:07:08,636 --> 05:07:17,163
And we were also able to receive the information that we've received, albeit in a fashion that maybe not satisfied many of us, but nonetheless got us through a process.

3413
05:07:17,843 --> 05:07:21,346
Now, quite frankly, for me, Madam President, this isn't about an organization.

3414
05:07:21,366 --> 05:07:24,028
This isn't about a corporation, all right?

3415
05:07:24,308 --> 05:07:25,590
This is about our city, all right?

3416
05:07:25,610 --> 05:07:26,390
This is about Medford.

3417
05:07:27,111 --> 05:07:27,891
It's about our neighbors.

3418
05:07:28,832 --> 05:07:30,934
It's about our family, our kids, all right?

3419
05:07:30,954 --> 05:07:35,258
It's about the men and women that go to work every day and try to make this city great.

3420
05:07:37,720 --> 05:07:44,805
And when we look at what's going on before COVID and since, we've seen an absolute HR nightmare.

3421
05:07:45,756 --> 05:07:48,218
when it comes to various department heads in this building.

3422
05:07:50,380 --> 05:07:57,025
We've seen the council call for quarterly meetings on the financial health of this community to no avail.

3423
05:07:58,206 --> 05:08:08,434
We've seen the council beg and plead for a copy of the monthly warrant articles, showing us where the money's being spent to the point where we've had to ask that the solicitor draft an ordinance for us.

3424
05:08:10,195 --> 05:08:14,719
When COVID hit, I thought it was the perfect opportunity for us to hit the reset button.

3425
05:08:16,381 --> 05:08:28,945
to look at some zero-based budgeting, where appropriations are actually based upon measurables, not a recycled budget from when Mr. Glione was the town manager, with little modifications throughout the last 40 years.

3426
05:08:33,266 --> 05:08:35,267
So here we are asking for information.

3427
05:08:36,627 --> 05:08:39,108
Between May and July, we virtually go undergoing.

3428
05:08:40,269 --> 05:08:44,810
And then come May and June, the council's got a seat at the table finally.

3429
05:08:46,216 --> 05:08:56,940
And when we finally have a seat at the table and we raise all those issues that we talked about for the last year, we get told any action other than a rubber stamp will be detrimental to this organization.

3430
05:09:00,642 --> 05:09:01,942
I don't think we can operate like this.

3431
05:09:04,123 --> 05:09:06,484
I don't think we can continue to afford to operate like this.

3432
05:09:06,804 --> 05:09:10,726
There's not a road in this street that you, not a road or a street in the city that you can drive down.

3433
05:09:11,887 --> 05:09:12,787
It's not in disrepair.

3434
05:09:14,954 --> 05:09:20,477
There's not a road or a street in this city that doesn't have a stump that's seven feet tall for some reason, but all the stumps are this tall.

3435
05:09:20,517 --> 05:09:21,937
They're gonna cut the tree down, cut the tree down.

3436
05:09:22,057 --> 05:09:23,698
I mean, come on, enough's enough, right?

3437
05:09:23,738 --> 05:09:25,399
I mean, the things are gigantic, right?

3438
05:09:25,699 --> 05:09:33,863
At the end of the day, you know, services have been degraded to the point where we have to hit the reset button.

3439
05:09:34,804 --> 05:09:38,946
And, you know, as I said, for me, this is about this city.

3440
05:09:39,966 --> 05:09:47,273
This is about our neighbors, our kids, our families, and the hard working men and women that go to work every day to make this city great.

3441
05:09:47,614 --> 05:09:49,255
Those are the people with their boots on the ground.

3442
05:09:49,736 --> 05:09:51,798
Those aren't the people with these things in front of their desks.

3443
05:09:52,118 --> 05:09:53,860
All right, we're not the ones that make the city great.

3444
05:09:54,120 --> 05:09:56,663
We make informed decisions to move that process along.

3445
05:09:56,983 --> 05:10:02,109
But it's the people in this room that were up here advocating and fighting for themselves that make the city great.

3446
05:10:02,189 --> 05:10:03,270
And they're what make a community.

3447
05:10:04,317 --> 05:10:06,919
And quite frankly, I think that this budget doesn't support that.

3448
05:10:07,580 --> 05:10:08,281
It misses the mark.

3449
05:10:08,941 --> 05:10:10,583
And for that reason, I won't be voting for it this evening.

3450
05:10:11,804 --> 05:10:12,544
Thank you, Councilor Knight.

3451
05:10:13,445 --> 05:10:15,547
Any further discussion from the council at this time?

3452
05:10:15,567 --> 05:10:20,852
I do see Director Hunt on Zoom who hasn't spoken yet, and then I'll go to you, Madam Chief of Staff.

3453
05:10:25,316 --> 05:10:27,118
Madam President, thank you very much.

3454
05:10:29,237 --> 05:10:32,159
Sorry for the late hour and my scratchy voice.

3455
05:10:32,979 --> 05:10:38,442
Can someone please explain what it means for the staff on July 1st if the staff, the council votes no?

3456
05:10:38,823 --> 05:10:41,784
There are actually a number of staff watching this evening.

3457
05:10:42,305 --> 05:10:47,968
Does the city close for 45 days and people get furloughed like the federal government until it goes into effect?

3458
05:10:48,388 --> 05:10:52,631
What are we supposed to tell the people that work for us tomorrow when we go into the office?

3459
05:10:53,411 --> 05:10:57,435
Um, or does the finance office have to create a one 12th budget in the next few days.

